Here's the standard approach:

### 1. Define each theme as a `ResourceDictionary`

```xml
<!-- Resources/Themes/LightTheme.xaml -->
<ResourceDictionary xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
                    xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml">
    <Color x:Key="PageBackground">#FFFFFF</Color>
    <Color x:Key="PrimaryText">#1A1A1A</Color>
    <Color x:Key="AccentColor">#0078D4</Color>
</ResourceDictionary>
```

Create matching `DarkTheme.xaml` and `HighContrastTheme.xaml` with the same keys but different values.

### 2. Swap themes at runtime

```csharp
public static class ThemeManager
{
    public enum AppTheme { Light, Dark, HighContrast }

    public static void ApplyTheme(AppTheme theme)
    {
        var mergedDicts = Application.Current!.Resources.MergedDictionaries;
        mergedDicts.Clear();

        var dictionary = theme switch
        {
            AppTheme.Dark         => new DarkTheme(),
            AppTheme.HighContrast => new HighContrastTheme(),
            _                     => new LightTheme(),
        };

        mergedDicts.Add(dictionary);

        // Persist the choice
        Preferences.Set("app_theme", theme.ToString());
    }

    public static void LoadSavedTheme()
    {
        var saved = Preferences.Get("app_theme", nameof(AppTheme.Light));
        if (Enum.TryParse<AppTheme>(saved, out var theme))
            ApplyTheme(theme);
    }
}
```

### 3. Apply saved theme on startup

In `App.xaml.cs`:

```csharp
public App()
{
    InitializeComponent();
    ThemeManager.LoadSavedTheme();
}
```

### 4. Settings page picker

```xml
<Picker x:Name="ThemePicker" Title="Theme"
        ItemsSource="{Binding ThemeOptions}"
        SelectedItem="{Binding SelectedTheme}"
        SelectedIndexChanged="OnThemeChanged" />
```

```csharp
void OnThemeChanged(object? sender, EventArgs e)
{
    if (ThemePicker.SelectedItem is string selected &&
        Enum.TryParse<ThemeManager.AppTheme>(selected, out var theme))
    {
        ThemeManager.ApplyTheme(theme);
    }
}
```

### 5. Consume theme colors in XAML

Use `DynamicResource` (not `StaticResource`) so values update when the dictionary is swapped:

```xml
<ContentPage BackgroundColor="{DynamicResource PageBackground}">
    <Label TextColor="{DynamicResource PrimaryText}" Text="Hello!" />
</ContentPage>
```

**Key points:**
- Same keys across all three dictionaries — only values differ.
- `DynamicResource` is essential; `StaticResource` won't react to swaps.
- `Preferences` persists the choice across launches.
